Dana Air said yesterday it has partnered with the Nigerian Economic Summit Group (NESG) towards the success of the 25th Nigerian Economic Summit holding today in Abuja. The theme for this year’s Summit is “Nigeria 2050: Shifting Gears,” and the focus is to set a new agenda for Nigeria as it ushers in the next industrial revolution and mark a critical strategic shift to a competitive private sector economy by 2050, Dana Air said in a statement by its spokesman, Mr. Kingsley Ezenwa. President Muhammadu Buhari, is expected to declare the 25th Nigerian Economic Summit open. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY There will be main plenary sessions, parallel breakout sessions, industry breakfast meetings, the annual Start-up Pitching and Venture Networking session as well as other activities to mark our Silver Jubilee. As airline partner of the 25th Nigerian Economic Summit, Dana Air said it would provide complimentary tickets and a special discount to guests and delegates to facilitate their transportation to the summit in Abuja. Ezenwa said, “As an Anniversary Event, NES #25 is unique because it marks a major milestone in our history of productive, robust and impactful public-private dialogues. Therefore, it is not just an opportunity to assess our progress and impact but, even more importantly, to project into the future.” Dana gives complimentary tickets to NES delegates Economic summit to focus on 2050 population prediction - NESG MMA2, Dana win airport, airline of the Year awards